Even if an experimental vaccine seems so far capable of reducing the mortality rate of Ebola, no remedy has yet been sufficiently effective to treat the existing infection.
Even though the administration of an antibody cocktail, ZMapp, initially showed promising signs in the field, formal studies have shown that its ability to limit deaths did not meet expectations.
In the PALM trial, ZMapp was used as a control, which means that the scientists used it as a reference point and compared it with the three other treatments.
The American Gymnastics Federation supports the letter from the United States Olympic Committee and accepts the absolute necessity for the Olympic family to promote a safe environment for all our athletes.
We agree with the statement of the USOC (United States Olympic Committee) that the interests of our athletes and our clubs, as well as their sport, could be better served. This can be done by moving forward and making significant changes within our organization, rather than revoking accreditation.
USA Gymnastics supports an independent investigation that could shed light on how the abuse of the scale described so bravely by the survivors of Larry Nassar could have gone unnoticed for so long and adopts any necessary and appropriate change.
USA Gymnastics and the USOC have the same goal: to make gymnastics, along with other sports, as safe as possible so that athletes can pursue their dreams in a safe, positive, and empowering environment.
